<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-271-057 </DOCNO><DOCID>08 589 554</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACKnowledge The Window Letter  Feb 26 1990 v2 n1 p1(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT ACKnowledge Press and the Windows TechnologyGroup 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Toolbook from Asymetrix. (Windows Watch) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Asymetrix Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   ToolBook (Program development software) (product introduction)Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (equipment andsupplies).andO;Topic:     Program Development ToolsSoftware EngineeringProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Initially, Apple didn't know what to do with Hypercard so they bundled itwith the Macintosh.andP;  Will Windows 3.0 power users know what to do withhypercard for Windows?andM;You bet they will! Toolbook from Asymetrix is a hypercard-like environmentthat will truly launch the graphical revolution.andP;  This is virtually anerector set for developers.andP;  We thought the Asymetrix demo we told you aboutlast year (November issue) was impressive.andP;  An object (a planet) is created,dragged around another object (Saturn) and the manipulation recorded andreproduced as an editable script.andP;  But that was nothing compared with whatToolbook will offer when it's announced in mid-May.andP;  We can't tell you aboutall its features yet, but be prepared for revolution ...andP;  and revolt amongMac developers.andP;  DOS is a market with ten times the potential of Mac.andP;  Andwith Toolbook, developers can prototype Windows applications without havingto decrypt the MS Windows SDK-and without having to pay royalties toAsymetrix.andM;On the corporate front, beta users are already building customized front endswith Toolbook.andP;  No, this software won't make a world-class programmer out ofgrandma, but it comes close.andP;  We'd love to wet your appetite by describingthe sample applications the folks at Asymetrix have put together.andP;  But wecan't .... except to say they are meant as templates, to be taken apart andused to construct your own application.andP;  (Thus the name 'Toolbook.') Look forToolbook to be announced In New York immediately following the MicrosoftWindows 3.O announcement.It will probably retail for $395.andM;Asymetrix Corporation, 110 110th Avenue NE, Suite 717, Bellevue, WA 98004;(206) 637-1567.andO;</TEXT></DOC>